June 18 (Reuters) - The following financial services industry appointment was announced on Wednesday. To inform us of other job changes, email to moves@thomsonreuters.com.

BANK OF AMERICA MERRILL LYNCH <BAC.N> William Egan, a co-head of the bank's global financial institutions group, has resigned to join credit investment and private equity firm Oaktree Capital Group LLC <OAK.N>, according to people familiar with the matter.